The letter is addressed to hospital administrators and expresses gratitude for their efforts in providing healthcare during the COVID-19 pandemic. The Trump Administration values their work and emphasizes the importance of the hospital's role in America's response to the virus. The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) and the Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) are coordinating the federal response, ensuring that state and local governments receive the necessary supplies and support. The letter requests hospitals to report data on COVID-19 cases to support epidemiological surveillance and public health decision making at the federal level. The Vice President, Michael R. Pence, signs the letter and expresses appreciation for the hospital's cooperation in obtaining the data needed for a robust state and federal response to the virus.